				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-1681463/ties-that-bind#post-4844992</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 14 Dec 2020 23:19:00 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>DarkStuff</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1581620</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>There is a part that has way too many mentions of &quot;below&quot; in a row that you can easily find with Ctrl+F, and two sentences that each use &quot;quickly&quot; one after the other, which leads to a very repetitious end to the Phineas/Anderson fight scene&#8230; but other than that small gripe, this was phenomenal. Great job, I love all these characters, and my intrigue for Anderson grows daily.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-1681463#post-4836233</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-1681463/ties-that-bind#post-4836233</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 04 Dec 2020 17:23:09 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Gaffsey</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>6590029</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Overall, well-written and enjoyable; it was nice to have some of the character fleshed (heh) out a bit. The only substantive complaint that I have is that while Anderson obviously progresses in terms of inhuman appearance throughout the flashbacks, he doesn't actually become more cold-blooded until the Isaac flashback, which makes it feel like a but of a jump.</p> <p>Still, quite good and sets up some interesting stuff in short order. +1</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
